    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bottom-dwelling marine invertebrates characterized by being covered by two valves or shells, with one valve covering the dorsal or topside and the other covering the ventral or bottom side; commonly known as lamp shells because they resemble early Roman oil lamps. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
